	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: FCEUX feature request</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Not a grid overlay, but the current interim build already has a &quot;show attributes&quot; toggle on the nametable viewer that I added to visualize attribute data. It also does now show attribute data and address for the mouse position in a &quot;properties&quot; display in the bottom right. There's also an &quot;ignore palettes&quot; feature that you can use to see the screen data even while the palette is black.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.emucr.com/2017/01/fceux-svn-r3330.html" class="postlink">http://www.emucr.com/2017/01/fceux-svn-r3330.html</a><br /><br />If you still want the grid, though, file a request on the sourceforge tracker. Maybe somebody will decide to do it. (Asking on this forum isn't the best way, though some FCEUX contributors do read it.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


